Library.description: SOA service library for Vendor Management Template in Active Workspace

DeprecationInfo.deprecatedDescription: assignPartnerContractToObject SOA will be versioned to assignPartnerContractToObject2 SOA to include the configuration context object in the input to assign the partner contract.

ParameterInfo.description: selected WorkspaceObject, partner contract to assign, preferred status.

Operation.description: This operation assigns the partner contract to the given WorkspaceObject object as specified in the input. The selected partner contract will be assigned to the given context information.
Operation.name: assignPartnerContractToObject
Operation.returnDescription:
The WorkspaceObject objects to which the partner contract is successfully assigned in the updated list. The following partial errors may be returned:

•    429002:    An object of type "Vm0PrtnrContractRevision" must be provided.

ParameterInfo.description: Context information consisting of a selected object,configuration context,partner contract to assign,and preferred status.

Operation.description: This operation assigns the partner contract to the given WorkspaceObject object as specified in the input. The selected partner contract will be assigned to the given context information.
Operation.name: assignPartnerContractToObject2
Operation.returnDescription:
The WorkspaceObject object to which the partner contract is successfully assigned in the updated list. The following partial errors may be returned:

•    429002:    An object of type "Partner Contract Revision" must be provided.
•    429003:    An object of type "Vendor Part" or "Item Revision" must be provided to assign.
•    429004:    The input preferred status is not valid. Valid values are given in LOV preference, “Vm0PrtnrContractAssignmentStatus”.
•    429005:    An object of type “Saved Bookmark” or “Session” must be provided for configuration context.

Operation.description: This operation returns the information of the assigned products of a given partner contract revision.
Operation.name: getAssignedProductsOfContract
Operation.returnDescription:
A list of ViewModelObject. Each ViewModelObject contains a model object and a list of view model properties.

The following partial errors may be returned:
•    429002: An object of type "Partner Contract Revision" must be provided

ParameterInfo.description: Type of table and WorkspaceObject business object.

Operation.description:
This operation returns the information of the columns for a given type of table to render a business object.

The column information returned as part of this operation includes display name, internal name, object type, width and a flag to indicate if the column needs to be displayed or not.
Operation.name: getColumnInfo
Operation.returnDescription:
Each ColumnInfo instance contains a display name, internal name, object type, width, and a flag to indicate if column needs to be displayed or not.
The following partial errors may be returned:
•    429001:     The input table type is not supported. The supported table type is "PartnersStructure".

Operation.description: This operation returns the information of the partner contracts of the selected object.
Operation.name: getPartnerContractsOfSelectedObject
Operation.returnDescription:
A list of ViewModelObject. Each ViewModelObject contains a model object and a list of view model properties.
The following partial errors may be returned:

•    429003:    An object of type “ManufacturerPart” or “ItemRevision” must be provided.

DeprecationInfo.deprecatedDescription: removePartnerContractFromObject SOA will be versioned to removePartnerContractFromObject2 SOA to include the list of selected Partner Contract in input which will allow to remove multiple Partner Contracts from WorkspaceObject.

ParameterInfo.description: The input structure contains the WorkspaceObject from which Partner Contract is to be removed and the Partner Contract which is to be removed.

Operation.description: This operation removes the partner contract from the given WorkspaceObject object as specified in the input. The selected partner contract will be removed from the given context information.
Operation.name: removePartnerContractFromObject
Operation.returnDescription:
The WorkspaceObject object from which the Partner Contract is successfully removed in the updated list. The following partial errors may be returned:

•    429003:    An object of type "Vendor Part" or "Item Revision" must be provided.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of RemovePartnerContractInput2 information consisting of selected objects and partner contract to remove.

Operation.description: This operation removes the partner contract from the given WorkspaceObject object as specified in the input. The partner contract will beis removed from the structure configuration of selected object. The selected object could be a ConfigurationContext or unconfigured ItemRevision.
Operation.name: removePartnerContractFromObject2
Operation.returnDescription:
The following partial errors may be returned:

•    429002:    An object of type "Partner Contract Revision" must be provided.
•    429003:    An object of type "Vendor Part" or "Item Revision" must be provided to assign.

ParameterInfo.description: Input criteria which includes view model objects, filter criteria and sort criteria.

A list of ViewModelObject and serviceData. Each ViewModelObject contains a model object and list of view model properties.

This operation returns the information of the columns for a table which is rendered as a part of tree table for given type of structure and business object.

The column information returned as part of this operation includes display name, internal name, object type, width and a flag to indicate if column needs to be displayed or not.
Struct.name: ColumnInfoResponse

StructElement.description: Internal name of the property on which column filter is applied.
StructElement.name: columnName

StructElement.description: The type of column filter operation applied. The supported operations are: “CONTAINS”, “EQUAL”, “GREATER THAN”, “LESS THAN” and “BETWEEN”.
StructElement.name: operation

StructElement.description:
A list of values to filter. These are not a fixed set of values like operation.
The "BETWEEN" operation is used only for Date type. It requires two values and the result will be the rows between the range given including min and max value. For example if min date is 2020-03-01T00:00:00+0530 and max date is 2020-03-05T00:00:00+0530, then the result will be shown from date 2020-03-01T00:00:00+0530 to 2020-03-05T00:00:00+0530.
StructElement.name: values

Struct.description: A structure representing the input filter criteria for columns.
Struct.name: FilterCriteriaInput

StructElement.description: A list of view model rows for each • displayed node in a table.
StructElement.name: viewModelRows

StructElement.description: A list of filters to be applied on the columns. The must be internal name of the properties on which filtering to be applied along with values of the filter must be sent as input.
StructElement.name: columnFilters

StructElement.description: A list of columns and the sort direction. The must be internal name of the property on which sorting to be applied along with sort direction.
StructElement.name: sortCriteria

Struct.description: The OrderedViewModelInput structure holds the information about the ViewModelObject structures and the information about filter criteria and sort criteria.
